          "merged_at": "2025-10-02T18:29:51Z"
        },
        "body": "This PR adds a Python version of the 09_HTTP_Packet project. It’s similar to the existing Java version, but written in Python so more people can understand and use it.\r\nThe server can handle:\r\n1) HTTP/1.0 – closes the connection after sending a response\r\n2) HTTP/1.1 – keeps the connection open by default\r\n3) HTTP/2.0 (simulated) – sends a simple response to mimic HTTP/2 behaviour\r\n\r\nIt supports these example paths:\r\n1) /success - returns \"Success!\"\r\n2) /error - returns \"Error: Not Found\"\r\n3) anything else - returns \"Bad Request\"\r\n\r\nThis change is useful in the following ways:\r\n1)Lets Python learners see how HTTP servers work.\r\n2)Makes the project accessible to more people, not just Java users.\r\n3)Uses only Python’s standard library so no extra installation is needed.\r\n\r\n",
